-(grunts, laughs)
-ALEX: What?

780
00:37:18.673 --> 00:37:19.822
TEDDY: Let's go!

781
00:37:19.905 --> 00:37:21.758
What's Fork Union?

782
00:37:21.841 --> 00:37:26.191
Uh, before, you said you don't
want to end up at Fork Union.

783
00:37:26.274 --> 00:37:29.601
It's a military academy in Virginia.

784
00:37:29.684 --> 00:37:32.406
That's where I'm going if I get
kicked out of school again.

785
00:37:32.489 --> 00:37:35.607
How many schools
have you been kicked out of?

786
00:37:35.690 --> 00:37:37.279
Three.

787
00:37:37.362 --> 00:37:39.105
That's why I'm still a junior.

788
00:37:39.188 --> 00:37:41.465
-Give or take a semester.
-ALEX: It's gone!

789
00:37:42.501 --> 00:37:43.945
My glove's gone.

790
00:37:44.028 --> 00:37:46.948
Twisted fucker orphaned
that glove on purpose.

791
00:37:47.031 --> 00:37:50.408
Left you with one so the loss
would sting that much more.

792
00:37:54.744 --> 00:37:57.206
♪ ♪

793
00:38:12.597 --> 00:38:14.811
♪ ♪

794
00:38:14.894 --> 00:38:17.226
(deep, shuddering breath)

795
00:38:32.111 --> 00:38:34.177
♪ ♪

796
00:38:48.292 --> 00:38:50.765
(crying)

797
00:38:59.974 --> 00:39:01.237
Hey.

798
00:39:02.449 --> 00:39:04.696
You all right?

799
00:39:04.779 --> 00:39:06.632
(voice shaking): I had a nightmare.

800
00:39:06.715 --> 00:39:08.766
I get nightmares too.

801
00:39:08.849 --> 00:39:11.197
I'm always falling or drowning.

802
00:39:11.280 --> 00:39:13.199
Also...

803
00:39:13.282 --> 00:39:15.201
(sobbing)

804
00:39:15.284 --> 00:39:17.154
I had an accident.

805
00:39:23.327 --> 00:39:25.112
Yeah, you did.

806
00:39:25.195 --> 00:39:27.884
Shh. Stop crying.

807
00:39:27.967 --> 00:39:30.491
If they hear you, they'll crucify you.

808
00:39:30.574 --> 00:39:33.219
Which would be ironic
since you're Buddhist.

809
00:39:33.302 --> 00:39:35.826
I know this is an excellent school,

810
00:39:35.909 --> 00:39:38.323
and my brothers went here,

811
00:39:38.406 --> 00:39:40.798
but I miss my family,

812
00:39:40.881 --> 00:39:43.114
and I have no friends.

813
00:39:44.150 --> 00:39:47.349
Yeah, well, friends are overrated.

814
00:39:48.825 --> 00:39:51.413
I'll help you hide the sheets
in the morning, all right?

815
00:39:51.496 --> 00:39:55.208
In the meantime, find a dry spot
and try to get some sleep.

816
00:39:55.291 --> 00:39:57.128
Thank you.

817
00:40:02.542 --> 00:40:04.443
Fucking asparagus.

818
00:40:27.633 --> 00:40:29.666
(clearing throat)

819
00:40:31.736 --> 00:40:33.378
(whispering): Are you kidding me?

820
00:40:33.461 --> 00:40:36.216
It's only 11:00, and he's already lit.

821
00:40:36.299 --> 00:40:38.053
I can smell the whiskey on him.

822
00:40:38.136 --> 00:40:40.693
Can you blame him? It's freezing in here.

823
00:40:40.776 --> 00:40:43.190
It's fucking Greenland in here.

824
00:40:43.273 --> 00:40:46.012
(helicopter whirring in distance)

825
00:40:59.060 --> 00:41:00.581
What the hell is that?

826
00:41:00.664 --> 00:41:02.732
(whirring continues)

827
00:41:25.790 --> 00:41:27.003
JASON: I knew it!

828
00:41:27.086 --> 00:41:29.561
He finally caved, the big softie.

829
00:41:30.861 --> 00:41:33.598
Hey, any of you guys like to ski?

830
00:41:35.030 --> 00:41:37.063
♪ ♪

831
00:41:38.704 --> 00:41:40.280
PAUL: Thank you.

832
00:41:40.363 --> 00:41:42.249
Goodbye, now.

833
00:41:42.332 --> 00:41:44.955
(chatter continues indistinctly)

834
00:41:45.038 --> 00:41:47.106
♪ ♪

835
00:41:48.945 --> 00:41:50.582
Yes!

836
00:41:57.085 --> 00:41:58.705
Well, good news, gentlemen.

837
00:41:58.788 --> 00:42:01.301
I was able to reach Dr. Woodrup
and your parents.

838
00:42:01.384 --> 00:42:03.826
Uh, most of them, anyway.

839
00:42:04.961 --> 00:42:07.340
Try calling again.
Just one more time, please.

840
00:42:07.423 --> 00:42:08.946
There's no point.

841
00:42:09.029 --> 00:42:10.651
The front desk says they're not answering.

842
00:42:10.734 --> 00:42:12.818
He says they're away on some excursion.

843
00:42:12.901 --> 00:42:14.886
-Excursion.
-(chuckles)

844
00:42:14.969 --> 00:42:17.526
I'm as disappointed as you are,
if not more so.

845
00:42:17.609 --> 00:42:19.561
I could have been spending
the rest of my vacation

846
00:42:19.644 --> 00:42:21.728
reading mystery novels.

847
00:42:21.811 --> 00:42:24.473
Maybe they're back now.
Just call again, please.

848
00:42:25.685 --> 00:42:27.146
Okay.

849
00:42:32.857 --> 00:42:34.367
Happy holidays.

850
00:42:34.450 --> 00:42:36.518
Same to you.

851
00:42:39.160 --> 00:42:41.160
Take care, Tully.

852
00:42:42.592 --> 00:42:44.817
I guess that just leaves you, huh?

853
00:42:44.900 --> 00:42:47.133
Be sure to do all your homework.

854
00:42:48.675 --> 00:42:50.218
Oh, almost forgot.

855
00:42:50.301 --> 00:42:52.468
I found that picture you were looking for.

856
00:42:53.636 --> 00:42:55.680
Merry Christmas, Mr. Tully.

857
00:42:58.443 --> 00:43:00.377
(Teddy laughing)

858
00:43:02.722 --> 00:43:04.381
Bye, Angus.

859
00:43:08.288 --> 00:43:11.173
♪ ♪

860
00:43:11.256 --> 00:43:13.324
(indistinct chatter)

861
00:43:34.479 --> 00:43:37.705
(Paul sighs)

862
00:43:37.788 --> 00:43:40.582
Well, let's make the best of it, shall we?

863
00:43:42.355 --> 00:43:44.239
(sighs)

864
00:43:44.322 --> 00:43:46.747
WOMAN (over TV): Oh, I suppose, um,

865
00:43:46.830 --> 00:43:48.716
-Stan Laurel, maybe, because...
-EUBANKS: Stan Laurel.

866
00:43:48.799 --> 00:43:50.784
All right. Your husband said
his favorite silent movie star

867
00:43:50.867 --> 00:43:53.622
is Rudolph Valentino.

868
00:43:53.705 --> 00:43:56.086
-Oh. He is good.
-MAN: Well, yeah.

869
00:43:56.169 --> 00:43:57.318
(laughter over TV)

870
00:43:57.401 --> 00:43:58.990
(Paul chuckles)

871
00:43:59.073 --> 00:44:00.585
EUBANKS: The last of our
five-point questions, girls...

872
00:44:00.668 --> 00:44:02.928
How about you? You ever been married?

873
00:44:03.011 --> 00:44:06.228
(scoffs, chuckles)

874
00:44:06.311 --> 00:44:08.637
No. I did get close once.

875
00:44:08.720 --> 00:44:10.771
Right after college.

876
00:44:10.854 --> 00:44:12.399
MARY: And?

877
00:44:12.482 --> 00:44:14.401
PAUL: We came to our senses.

878
00:44:14.484 --> 00:44:19.076
This is not exactly a face
forged for romance, Mary.

879
00:44:19.159 --> 00:44:21.782
Yeah, and the...

880
00:44:21.865 --> 00:44:23.575
And, you know...

881
00:44:23.658 --> 00:44:24.901
What?

882
00:44:25.970 --> 00:44:27.689
Nothing.

883
00:44:27.772 --> 00:44:30.692
I don't know. I like being alone.

884
00:44:30.775 --> 00:44:34.190
I've always found myself drawn
to the aesthetic.

885
00:44:34.273 --> 00:44:36.093
Like a monk.

886
00:44:36.176 --> 00:44:38.359
The forgoing of sensual pleasures

887
00:44:38.442 --> 00:44:40.295
for the achievement of spiritual goals.

888
00:44:40.378 --> 00:44:41.802
-Spiritual goals?
-Mm-hmm.

889
00:44:41.885 --> 00:44:43.364
-You?
-(chuckles)

890
00:44:43.447 --> 00:44:44.805
What spiritual goals are we talking about?

891
00:44:44.888 --> 00:44:46.169
You go to church?

892
00:44:46.252 --> 00:44:48.171
-Mm, only when required.
-Exactly.

893
00:44:48.254 --> 00:44:50.470
When's the last time you even left campus?

894
00:44:50.553 --> 00:44:52.472
-I go into town all the time.
-Oh.

895
00:44:52.555 --> 00:44:54.474
For groceries and various errands

896
00:44:54.557 --> 00:44:55.981
-and appointments.
-Mm-hmm.

897
00:44:56.064 --> 00:44:58.280
(sighs, stammers)

898
00:44:58.363 --> 00:45:01.151
Okay, yes, I don't leave campus often.

899
00:45:01.234 --> 00:45:02.647
I don't really feel the need.

900
00:45:02.730 --> 00:45:04.385
Let me ask you something.

901
00:45:04.468 --> 00:45:07.828
If you could go anywhere
on Earth, where would you go?

902
00:45:07.911 --> 00:45:09.357
(chuckling): Oh.

903
00:45:09.440 --> 00:45:11.700
Greece, Italy,

904
00:45:11.783 --> 00:45:14.703
Egypt, Peru, Carthage.

905
00:45:14.786 --> 00:45:16.804
Tunisia now, of course.

906
00:45:16.887 --> 00:45:19.367
In college, I started
a monograph on Carthage.

907
00:45:19.450 --> 00:45:22.205
I'd like to finish that someday.

908
00:45:22.288 --> 00:45:25.846
(sighs) A monograph is
like a book, o-only shorter.

909
00:45:25.929 --> 00:45:28.013
I know what a monograph is.

910
00:45:28.096 --> 00:45:30.164
Why not just write a book?

911
00:45:31.871 --> 00:45:34.531
I'm not sure I have an entire book in me.

912
00:45:36.106 --> 00:45:39.206
You can't even dream
a whole dream, can you?

913
00:45:41.441 --> 00:45:43.980
(grunting softly)

914
00:45:47.645 --> 00:45:49.546
(groans)

915
00:46:00.900 --> 00:46:02.278
(sighs)

916
00:46:02.361 --> 00:46:04.753
Monet, Manet, Picasso.

917
00:46:04.836 --> 00:46:06.838
(passes gas)

918
00:46:10.338 --> 00:46:13.009
(takes deep breath)

919
00:46:16.916 --> 00:46:18.982
(Paul snoring)

920
00:46:33.493 --> 00:46:36.527
("Crying, Laughing, Loving,
Lying" by Labi Siffre playing)

921
00:46:41.402 --> 00:46:43.941
♪ Crying ♪

922
00:46:46.011 --> 00:46:50.772
♪ Crying never did nobody no good no how ♪

923
00:46:55.086 --> 00:46:57.218
♪ That's why I ♪

924
00:47:00.058 --> 00:47:03.521
♪ I don't cry ♪

925
00:47:08.132 --> 00:47:10.935
♪ Laughing ♪

926
00:47:12.697 --> 00:47:17.436
♪ Laughing sometimes does
somebody some good somehow ♪

927
00:47:19.440 --> 00:47:21.946
♪ That's why I ♪

928
00:47:23.983 --> 00:47:27.644
♪ I'm laughing now ♪

929
00:47:29.054 --> 00:47:31.549
♪ That's why I ♪

930
00:47:33.388 --> 00:47:37.258
♪ I'm laughing now. ♪

931
00:47:50.141 --> 00:47:52.174
(song ends)

932
00:48:14.297 --> 00:48:16.808
(takes deep breath)

933
00:48:16.891 --> 00:48:18.365
<i>(Paul clears throat)</i>

934
00:48:19.368 --> 00:48:21.137
I have a surprise.

935
00:48:23.108 --> 00:48:25.652
Uh, these were a gift to me,

936
00:48:25.735 --> 00:48:28.804
and I would like to share them
with both of you.

937
00:48:29.873 --> 00:48:32.362
Look at them.
Look at all the festive shapes.

938
00:48:32.445 --> 00:48:35.596
Snowflakes and gingerbread men. A tree.

939
00:48:35.679 --> 00:48:38.203
A little mitten. (chuckles)

940
00:48:38.286 --> 00:48:40.552
Mmm. (chuckles)

941
00:48:41.984 --> 00:48:43.456
Mmm.

942
00:48:44.492 --> 00:48:46.442
May I go to the bathroom, sir?

943
00:48:46.525 --> 00:48:48.362
You may.

944
00:48:51.829 --> 00:48:53.350
(sighs)

945
00:48:53.433 --> 00:48:55.220
Well, I'm trying.

946
00:48:55.303 --> 00:48:57.371
(laughing)

947
00:48:59.969 --> 00:49:01.292
Mmm.

948
00:49:01.375 --> 00:49:02.887
If you don't have a single room,

949
00:49:02.970 --> 00:49:04.757
uh, I'll take a junior suite
or the equivalent.

950
00:49:04.840 --> 00:49:06.726
I fully understand it's the holidays,

951
00:49:06.809 --> 00:49:08.365
but it's kind of an emergency.

952
00:49:08.448 --> 00:49:10.235
Mm-hmm. Yeah, sure.

953
00:49:10.318 --> 00:49:11.731
Mr. Tully, what are you doing?

954
00:49:11.814 --> 00:49:13.139
Uh, no, no credit card.

955
00:49:13.222 --> 00:49:14.536
I'll pay cash or traveler's checks.

956
00:49:14.619 --> 00:49:15.867
I didn't say you could use the phone.

957
00:49:15.950 --> 00:49:17.374
(chuckling): Okay, I see.

958
00:49:17.457 --> 00:49:18.375
Is there anywhere else
you could recommend?

959
00:49:18.458 --> 00:49:19.948
Maybe downtown or...

960
00:49:20.031 --> 00:49:22.049
-Was that a hotel?
-None of your business.

961
00:49:22.132 --> 00:49:25.052
It is absolutely my business.
I'm looking after you.

962
00:49:25.135 --> 00:49:26.911
Looking after me? Really?

963
00:49:26.994 --> 00:49:28.990
-Like what? Like my warden?
-(scoffs)

964
00:49:29.073 --> 00:49:30.552
Like my butler?

965
00:49:30.635 --> 00:49:32.422
There's nobody here, okay?

966
00:49:32.505 --> 00:49:34.325
Just us two losers and a grieving mom.

967
00:49:34.408 --> 00:49:36.063
So let's cut the shit.

968
00:49:36.146 --> 00:49:38.065
You stay out of my way,
and I'll stay out of yours.

969
00:49:38.148 --> 00:49:39.924
-That's a detention.
-(groans)

970
00:49:40.007 --> 00:49:41.629
You just earned yourself a detention, sir.

971
00:49:41.712 --> 00:49:43.433
Now, get back here!

972
00:49:43.516 --> 00:49:46.337
Being here with you is already
one big fucking detention!

973
00:49:46.420 --> 00:49:48.900
Son of a bitch, that's another detention!

974
00:49:48.983 --> 00:49:50.671
("Deck the Halls" by
The Swingle Singers playing)

975
00:49:50.754 --> 00:49:52.030
Mr. Tully!

976
00:49:53.957 --> 00:49:56.248
I don't know what you're
playing at, Mr. Tully,

977
00:49:56.331 --> 00:49:58.745
but you are courting disaster!

978
00:49:58.828 --> 00:50:01.319
Without exercise, the body devours itself.

979
00:50:01.402 --> 00:50:04.124
You are careening towards suspension!

980
00:50:04.207 --> 00:50:05.703
(grumbles)

981
00:50:09.115 --> 00:50:11.148
(panting)

982
00:50:16.155 --> 00:50:18.221
(panting heavily)

983
00:50:30.994 --> 00:50:33.153
Don't even think about it, Mr. Tully.

984
00:50:33.236 --> 00:50:37.289
You are a hair's breadth from suspension.

985
00:50:37.372 --> 00:50:40.160
I'll wash my hands of you, you hear me?

986
00:50:40.243 --> 00:50:42.245
Wash my hands.

987
00:50:45.107 --> 00:50:46.727
Stop right there.

988
00:50:46.810 --> 00:50:50.011
You know the gym is strictly off-limits.

989
00:50:51.421 --> 00:50:53.305
This is your Rubicon.

990
00:50:53.388 --> 00:50:56.688
Do not cross the Rubicon.

991
00:51:00.463 --> 00:51:02.760
<i>Alea jacta est.</i>

992
00:51:09.703 --> 00:51:12.473
(Angus screaming)

993
00:51:16.314 --> 00:51:18.594
Oh, fuck! Ow!

994
00:51:18.677 --> 00:51:21.317
Jesus, Mr. Hunham! Fuck!

995
00:51:22.485 --> 00:51:23.896
Hurry up! Hurry!

996
00:51:23.979 --> 00:51:25.931
I am hurrying!

997
00:51:26.014 --> 00:51:27.669
I was on thin ice already.

998
00:51:27.752 --> 00:51:29.902
If Woodrup finds out,
the facts won't matter.

999
00:51:29.985 --> 00:51:31.904
-He'll make it my fault.
-It is your fault!

1000
00:51:31.987 --> 00:51:33.873
You were supposed to be looking after me.

1001
00:51:33.956 --> 00:51:35.512
I told you to stop.

1002
00:51:35.595 --> 00:51:37.250
You said you washed your hands of me.

1003
00:51:37.333 --> 00:51:38.713
No, I meant it metaphorically!

1004
00:51:38.796 --> 00:51:40.715
Of course you meant it metaphorically.

1005
00:51:40.798 --> 00:51:43.751
What were you going to do,
actually go and wash your hands?

1006
00:51:43.834 --> 00:51:45.621
This is the end.

1007
00:51:45.704 --> 00:51:48.052
They'll inform the school
who will inform your parents,

1008
00:51:48.135 --> 00:51:49.592
and then it's curtains.

1009
00:51:49.675 --> 00:51:51.363
(chuckles)

1010
00:51:51.446 --> 00:51:53.860
You're gonna get me fired.

1011
00:51:53.943 --> 00:51:56.236
You. (scoffs)

1012
00:51:56.319 --> 00:51:57.897
I'm the one that might lose an arm,

1013
00:51:57.980 --> 00:52:00.240
and all you can think about is yourself.

1014
00:52:00.323 --> 00:52:01.868
NURSE: If you could fill this out, please.

1015
00:52:01.951 --> 00:52:03.689
Admissions and insurance.

1016
00:52:06.265 --> 00:52:08.644
(Paul sighs)

1017
00:52:08.727 --> 00:52:10.366
Excuse me.

1018
00:52:12.502 --> 00:52:15.981
Is there any way we could skip
this whole insurance thing?

1019
00:52:16.064 --> 00:52:17.719
It's just standard procedure.

1020
00:52:17.802 --> 00:52:19.457
ANGUS: I understand, but look, um,

1021
00:52:19.540 --> 00:52:21.723
we were over at Squantz Pond
playing hockey,

1022
00:52:21.806 --> 00:52:23.164
and I slipped on the ice.

1023
00:52:23.247 --> 00:52:24.792
Angus, what are you doing?

1024
00:52:24.875 --> 00:52:27.795
My mom told him not to take me,
but I made him.

1025
00:52:27.878 --> 00:52:29.302
My folks are divorced.

1026
00:52:29.385 --> 00:52:31.062
We don't get to see each other very often.

1027
00:52:31.145 --> 00:52:33.306
She'll be mad as a hornet
if she finds out.

1028
00:52:33.389 --> 00:52:34.802
NURSE: Okay, that's your business,

1029
00:52:34.885 --> 00:52:36.507
but we just have certain protocols.

1030
00:52:36.590 --> 00:52:38.245
-Yeah. Protocols.
-Please.

1031
00:52:38.328 --> 00:52:40.148
I never get to see my dad.

1032
00:52:40.231 --> 00:52:42.645
It was my fault. All mine.

1033
00:52:42.728 --> 00:52:45.186
I don't want to get him in any trouble.

1034
00:52:45.269 --> 00:52:47.980
I don't want her dragging you
into court again.

1035
00:52:48.063 --> 00:52:50.257
We can skip the insurance thing.

1036
00:52:50.340 --> 00:52:52.622
We can pay cash.

1037
00:52:52.705 --> 00:52:54.921
Right, Dad?

1038
00:52:55.004 --> 00:52:57.264
DOCTOR: So the good news is
nothing's broken,

1039
00:52:57.347 --> 00:52:59.926
but you did dislocate
your shoulder pretty badly.

1040
00:53:00.009 --> 00:53:01.796
What does that mean?

1041
